One-Line Summary (for resume header under project name)
Containerized and deployed a full-stack MERN bookstore application on Kubernetes with real-time monitoring, auto-scaling, self-healing, and alerting using Prometheus and Grafana.

Bullet Points (use 6–8 of these under the project)
Containerized a full-stack MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js) Online Bookstore application using Docker, creating optimized multi-stage Dockerfiles for both frontend (React + Nginx) and backend (Node.js) services, reducing final image size significantly by separating build and runtime stages
Deployed the application on a Kubernetes (Minikube) cluster with 4 running pods (2 backend + 2 frontend replicas) using YAML manifests for Deployments, Services (ClusterIP & NodePort), Namespaces, and Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA)
Configured Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA) to automatically scale backend pods from 2 to 5 replicas when CPU utilization exceeds 70%, ensuring the application handles traffic spikes without manual intervention
Demonstrated Kubernetes self-healing by forcefully deleting running pods and verifying automatic recreation within 10 seconds, proving fault tolerance and zero-downtime recovery
Installed and configured the full kube-prometheus-stack monitoring suite via Helm (single command deployment), including Prometheus, Grafana, Alertmanager, Node Exporter, and Kube State Metrics
Built real-time Grafana dashboards (Dashboard ID: 15760) connected to Prometheus as data source, visualizing live CPU usage, memory consumption, pod status, resource requests/limits, and pod IP addresses across all bookstore pods
Wrote PromQL queries in Prometheus to monitor container memory usage per pod — verified backend pods consuming ~36MB and frontend pods consuming ~10MB in real time
Configured 3 custom PrometheusRule alert rules (PodDown — Critical, HighMemoryUsage — Warning at 200MB, HighCPUUsage — Warning at 80%) deployed as Kubernetes CRD resources using kubectl
Pushed Docker images to Docker Hub (adhithya143/bookstore-backend:v1, adhithya143/bookstore-frontend:v1) making them publicly accessible for Kubernetes to pull during pod deployment
Built a secure REST API backend with JWT authentication, 8 protected API endpoints (CRUD operations for books and users), connected to MongoDB Atlas cloud database with Mongoose ODM
Managed the entire DevOps pipeline from code to deployment: Git sparse clone → Dockerize → Push to registry → Kubernetes deployment → Helm monitoring stack → Alert configuration
